        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:22PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles southwest of Hugo to 10 miles
southwest of Thurman, or extending from 16 miles southeast of Limon
to 24 miles northeast of Limon, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hugo and Arriba.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with these storms and may lead to flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
